mg: mg (portable Micro Emacs clone)
mg:
mg: Mg is a Micro Emacs clone created in 1987, based on MicroEMACS v30.
mg: Fully free and in the public domain, the intention is to be a small,
mg: fast, and portable Emacs-like editor for users who cannot, or do not
mg: want to, run the real Emacs for one reason or another.
mg:
mg: Compatibility with GNU Emacs is key for Mg, separating it from other
mg: ErsatzEmacs clones, because there should never be any reason to
mg: learn more than one Emacs flavor.
mg: Homepage: https://github.com/troglobit/mg
